er electrical devices that heat, such as heat tape and heaters, can do that=
. It could also be some other faulty electrical device. It could be a bad w=
iring connection or even a bad power meter (I had that happen last winter).=


  Those touch lamps usually use some sort of CMOS IC or MOSFET device tha=
t is sensitive to capacitance. Touching the base adds capacitance that they=
 sense and switch as a result. Those devices have a lifetime of maybe 5 to =
10 years from my experience and start switching on their own at random.

